# TyG Research Dashboard – Cursor AI Rules
# Dr. Muddu Surendra Nehru, Professor of Medicine, HOMA Clinic

## ⚠️ GOLDEN RULE: 3 Papers, Zero Confusion

### Paper 1: ✅ PUBLISHED (READ-ONLY)
- Journal: J Contemp Clin Pract 2025;11(8):349-357
- DOI: 10.61336/jccp/25-08-50
- Action: Display badge + DOI link ONLY

### Paper 2: 📤 SUBMITTED (READ-ONLY)
- Data: 60 patients, manuscript written, submitted
- Action: Display submission status ONLY

### Paper 3: 🧪 NEW – TyG-HbA1c (ACTIVE)
- Action: Full development, manuscript generation, export

## When I Request Changes:
1. ALWAYS ask: "Which paper? 1 (Published), 2 (Submitted), or 3 (Active)?"
2. If 1 or 2: Respond "⚠️ Read-only. No changes allowed."
3. If 3: Proceed with NEW files only, never modify Paper 1/2 files

## Never Modify:
- lib/utils/ijcpr-manuscript.ts (Paper 1)
- Any submitted manuscript files (Paper 2)
- Patient type core fields (add optional only)

## Always Confirm:
"✅ Paper 1 & 2 unchanged. Paper 3 only."

---

## Reference (unchanged behavior)

### Paper 1 ONLY
- app/published, components/published/* – display + DOI only. No patientData, no export, no edit.

### Paper 2 ONLY
- app/submitted – submission status only. No regeneration, no export, no edit.

### Paper 3 ONLY
- lib/utils/hba1c-manuscript.ts, Tab5JCDR (Write JCDR). Full edit → generate → export.

### Shared
- lib/types/patient.ts: optional fields only (e.g. hba1c?). TabExtract: data entry + table. Tab2Verify, stats-calculator: unchanged unless adding optional support.

### Red Flags
- "Update manuscript for new data" → Which paper? Paper 3 only.
- "Add export for Paper 1" → ⚠️ Read-only.
- "Merge Paper 2 and 3" → ⚠️ Papers stay separate.
- "Remove optional Patient fields" → ⚠️ Add only.
- lab() in CSS → Use hsl() only.

### Don't destroy success
Add or fix in a minimal, safe way. Backend → frontend. Test before changing.
